			======================================
				Installing Dazuko Filter
				    A Quick Guide
			======================================

1. Requirements
	
	* Compiled RedirFS Framework - follow the RedirFS install file
	* Correspondent Dazuko source code - download from www.dazuko.org

2. Download
	
	* Get the latest patch at http://www.redirfs.org/packages/dazukoflt_patch-x.y.z.tar.gz

3. Compilation
	
	* Unpack package
		$ tar -xvzf dazukoflt_path-x.y.z.tar.gz

	* Copy Dazukoflt patch to Dazuko source directory
		$ cp dazukoflt_patch-x.y.z/dazukoflt-x.y.z.patch <Dazuko source code directory>
	
	* Patch Dazuko source code
		$ cd <Dazuko source code directory>
		$ patch -p1 < dazukoflt-x.y.z.patch

	* Configure Dazuko with RedirFS support (see ./configure --help)
		$ ./configure --enable-redirfs --redirfs-path=<patch to the RedirFS source directory>

	* Compile Dazuko
		$ make

4. Inserting Dazuko Filter module
	Note: The RedirFS module has to be already loaded in Linux kernel
	
	* Change user to root
		$ su

	* Insert module
		# insmod dazuko.ko

5. Problems & Bugs

	* Can be reported to Bugzilla at http://www.redirfs.org/cgi-bin/bugzilla/index.cgi
